item.title: The Contenders, Vol. 20: The Beths, Dustin O’Halloran, Nicholas Payton, more
item.description:
We’ve got six must-hear songs to add to our running list of the year’s best tracks, including some shredding from The Beths, a gorgeous solo piano piece from Dustin O’Halloran, sublime jazz from Nicholas Payton and more.

Featured artists and songs:


1. The Beths: “No Joy,” from ‘Straight Line Was A Lie’

2. Nate Smith & Saje: “Big Fish,” from ‘Live Action’

3. Dustin O’Halloran: “Gold” (Single)

item.title: Strongest evidence yet for past life on Mars; The Romans impact on the British economy; Link between exercise and your microbiome
item.description: Episode 320 Was Mars once home to alien life? The evidence is stronger than ever, since NASA’s discovery of rocks marked by patterns similar to those made by microbes on Earth. Found in an area now named “Bright Angel”, these rocks give us a tantalising insight into Mars’ ancient past - but just how definitive is this finding? It’s long been thought that when the Roman Empire withdrew from Britain in the early 400s, the result was chaos and economic collapse - leading us into the “Dark Ages”...
